Proper noun

[edit]

Woodburn (countable and uncountable, plural Woodburns)

A surname.

A place name:

A town in Richmond Valley council area, New South Wales, Australia.

A community in Pictou County, Nova Scotia, Canada.

A neighbourhood of Dalkeith, Midlothian council area, Scotland (OS grid ref NT3467). [1]

A place in the United States:

An unincorporated community in Bunker Hill Township, Macoupin County, Illinois.

A city in Maumee Township, Allen County, Indiana.

A minor city in Clarke County, Iowa.

A minor city in Warren County, Kentucky.

A city in Marion County, Oregon.

Statistics

[edit]

According to the 2010 United States Census, Woodburn is the 11807th most common surname in the United States, belonging to 2651 individuals. Woodburn is most common among White (89.21%) individuals.
